    <h2>Wind Direction</h2>
    <p>The <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wind_direction" target="_blank">Wind Direction</a> is reported by the direction from which it originates. For example, a northerly wind blows from the north to the south.  The wind directions are measured in units from 0° to 360°. Wind direction is measured in degrees clockwise from due north. A wind blowing from the north has a wind direction of 0° (360°), a wind blowing from the east has a wind direction of 90°, a wind blowing from the south has a wind direction of 180°, and a wind blowing from the west has a wind direction of 270°. See details below.</p>
